<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1373,1398]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is in honor of the American salticidologist G.B. Edwards, to celebrate his recent contribution to the understanding of systematics of freyines. Female in gender, ending in -ya taken from 
<taxonomicName authority="C.L. Koch" authorityName="C.L. Koch" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Freya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1314,1380,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Freya</emphasis>
C.L. Koch
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus box="[225,273,1446,1470]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">type</typeStatus>
genus of the subtribe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1481,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Relationships.</emphasis>
This lineage seems to be related to the also Amazonian ground dwellers 
<taxonomicName authority="Galiano" authorityName="Galiano" box="[1206,1436,1481,1506]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kalcerrytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1339,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Kalcerrytus</emphasis>
Galiano
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Brescovit" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Brescovit" box="[198,478,1517,1542]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Onofre" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,276,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Onofre</emphasis>
Ruiz &amp; Brescovit
</taxonomicName>
by the general appearance (dark body with light chevrons on abdomen, 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1380,1517,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 5, 8</figureCitation>
), the apophysis on the venter of the male palpal femur (
<collectionCode box="[733,791,1554,1578]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/rqv1-d99c" name="HHS/FDA" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">FDA</collectionCode>
in 
<figureCitation box="[831,919,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[933,963,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">46</figureCitation>
) and the stout RTA (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1336,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 11–14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1350,1424,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">46–47</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Brescovit" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Brescovit" box="[151,474,1589,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edilemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1589,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edilemma</emphasis>
Ruiz &amp; Brescovit
</taxonomicName>
also has a developed 
<collectionCode box="[730,789,1590,1614]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/rqv1-d99c" name="HHS/FDA" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">FDA</collectionCode>
, although its color pattern resembles more that of 
<taxonomicName authority="C.L. Koch" authorityName="C.L. Koch" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Freya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1370,1436,1590,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Freya</emphasis>
C.L. Koch
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[282,427,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">sensu stricto</emphasis>
. Similarities in general appearance and external reproductive structures with 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon" authorityName="Simon" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Capidava" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Capidava</emphasis>
Simon
</taxonomicName>
, another Amazonian ground dwelling freyine, could also be due to phylogenetic relationship, although this is less likely.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among freyines, males of 
<taxonomicName box="[628,753,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[628,753,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edwardsya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1050,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kalcerrytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[918,1050,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Kalcerrytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1143,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Onofre" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1064,1143,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Onofre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1312,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edilemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1312,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edilemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for having a developed femoral distal apophysis in the palp (
<collectionCode box="[722,780,1770,1794]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/rqv1-d99c" name="HHS/FDA" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">FDA</collectionCode>
in 
<figureCitation box="[819,907,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[920,951,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">46</figureCitation>
), but can be recognized by the developed, triangular terminal apophysis (TmA in 
<figureCitation box="[591,719,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 10–12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[731,805,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">44–45</figureCitation>
), absent in the other three. Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1240,1372,1805,1829]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kalcerrytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1240,1372,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Kalcerrytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[193,455,1841,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit A. D. (2003) Description of six new species of Kalcerrytus Galiano from the Brazilian Amazon (Araneae: Salticidae). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia, 8, 73 - 79." type="journal article" year="2003">Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bustamante" box="[539,826,1841,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Bustamante, A. A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S. (2016) Three new species of Kalcerrytus Galiano, 2000 from Brazil (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 4066 (1), 41 - 51. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4066.1.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Bustamante &amp; Ruiz 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 9) and 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1036,1841,1865]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Onofre" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[958,1036,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Onofre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[1095,1357,1841,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2007) Onofre, a new genus of jumping spider from Brazil (Araneae, Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 14, 77 - 80. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2007.14.2.77" type="journal article" year="2007">Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5) have accessory pockets laterally on the epigynal plate, but these structures are not present in 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1340,1877,1901]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1215,1340,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edwardsya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1356,1431,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,183,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">43</figureCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[331,445,1913,1937]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edilemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[331,445,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edilemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have advanced ventral coupling pockets on the epigyne (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[1126,1389,1913,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2006) Edilemma, a new genus of jumping spider from Tocantins, Brazil (Araneae, Salticidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 23, 364 - 366. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752006000200008" type="journal article" year="2006">Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 2006</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5), while 
<taxonomicName box="[257,382,1949,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[257,382,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Edwardsya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have dorsal coupling pockets (
<figureCitation box="[730,816,1949,1974]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[828,860,1950,1974]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
