<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1337,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1985,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Description.</emphasis>
Moderately small to medium-sized (males 5.68–5.91, females 6.14–6.22), ground dwelling jumping spiders from the Amazon. Carapace dark brown with a pair of lateral stripes of white scales, more conspicuous in males (
<figureCitation box="[409,511,188,213]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,661,1766]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[151,1436,661,1767]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 4. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., live male from Belém. © W. P. Maddison, under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license." captionText-1="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/164520/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 1–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[525,598,188,212]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 35 – 38" captionStart-1="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId-0="9.[151,264,1504,1527]" captionStartId-1="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId-0="figure@9.[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetId-1="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId-0="9" captionTargetPageId-1="10" captionText-0="FIGURES 35 – 38. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 35 male left chelicera, retrolateral; 36 long, white scales of dorsal male palpal femur; 37 white scales forming the stripe on lateral carapace; 38 same, detail." captionText-1="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/263815/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">37–39</figureCitation>
), and sparse white (
<figureCitation box="[825,908,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1156]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 31 reddish scales on male head, dorsal; 32 dark scales on male head, lateral; 33 white scales on male carapace; 34 epiandrous fusules, ventral (arrows)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263814/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) and dark (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1122,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1156]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 31 reddish scales on male head, dorsal; 32 dark scales on male head, lateral; 33 white scales on male carapace; 34 epiandrous fusules, ventral (arrows)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263814/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) scales; males with reddish scales on head (
<figureCitation box="[331,433,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,661,1767]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., live male from Belém. © W. P. Maddison, under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164520/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[447,477,224,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1156]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 31 reddish scales on male head, dorsal; 32 dark scales on male head, lateral; 33 white scales on male carapace; 34 epiandrous fusules, ventral (arrows)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263814/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">31</figureCitation>
), bright when alive. Chelicera similar in both sexes, with two promarginal teeth and one retromarginal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[433,517,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1504,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 38. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 35 male left chelicera, retrolateral; 36 long, white scales of dorsal male palpal femur; 37 white scales forming the stripe on lateral carapace; 38 same, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263815/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Male endite with strong disto-ectal corrugated apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1330,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1660,1683]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1639]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 25 male endites, dorsal; 26 apophysis on left endite; 27 same, detail; 28 same, detail of distal portion; 29 apophysis on right endite; 30 same, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263813/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 25–30</figureCitation>
). Labium rounded and sternum oval. Male palpal femur with a distal proventral apophysis and dorsal tuft of long, white scales (
<figureCitation box="[234,308,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,661,1767]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., live male from Belém. © W. P. Maddison, under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164520/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[322,354,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1504,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,519,1483]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 38. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 35 male left chelicera, retrolateral; 36 long, white scales of dorsal male palpal femur; 37 white scales forming the stripe on lateral carapace; 38 same, detail." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263815/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">36</figureCitation>
); short tibia with a strong, curved RTA (
<figureCitation box="[816,945,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 11–14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[958,1031,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., left male palp. 21 tibia, distal (cymbium removed); 22 RTA, ventral; 23 – 24 bulb (23 retrodorsal; 24 dorso-distal); E = embolus; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; T = tegulum; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">21–22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1044,1115,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">46–47</figureCitation>
) and poorly developed PTA (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., left male palp. 21 tibia, distal (cymbium removed); 22 RTA, ventral; 23 – 24 bulb (23 retrodorsal; 24 dorso-distal); E = embolus; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; T = tegulum; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); shoe-shaped cymbium, well developed functional tegulum, embolar base with a prolateral process (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[237,311,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">44–45</figureCitation>
), and terminal apophysis long and triangular, folded to receive the embolus (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1290,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1304,1377,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,951,1915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., left male palp. 21 tibia, distal (cymbium removed); 22 RTA, ventral; 23 – 24 bulb (23 retrodorsal; 24 dorso-distal); E = embolus; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; T = tegulum; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">23–24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1391,1423,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">45</figureCitation>
); functionally it appears to be a secondary conductor. Leg formula 3412 or 
<quantity box="[972,1057,439,464]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.095248" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" unit="in" value="4312.0">4312 in</quantity>
both sexes. Leg I dark brown, II– IV yellow or light brown. Abdomen about the same length of carapace, dark brown, with anterior transverse light stripe and dorsal chevrons (
<figureCitation box="[462,563,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 5, 8</figureCitation>
), reddish in live males (
<figureCitation box="[836,938,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1788,1811]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,661,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,661,1767]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov., live male from Belém. © W. P. Maddison, under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164520/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
); anterodorsal scutum in males (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1378,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1391,1422,512,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">39</figureCitation>
); males with epiandrous fusules (
<figureCitation box="[506,591,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1156]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 34. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 31 reddish scales on male head, dorsal; 32 dark scales on male head, lateral; 33 white scales on male carapace; 34 epiandrous fusules, ventral (arrows)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263814/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Epigyne with a pair of round copulatory openings placed anteriorly and a dorsal coupling pocket (
<figureCitation box="[421,494,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1696,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,433,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,411,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 9. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 5 male, dorsal; 6 – 7 left male palp (6 ventral; 7 retrolateral); 8 female, dorsal; 9 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263809/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[505,577,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">15–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[590,620,584,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[632,707,584,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">48–49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
